<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-25T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-25T10:00:00-05:00" n="55" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1812</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-25T16:00:00+01:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 25, 1915, 4 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 4.20 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>296. Austrian and German Ambassadors both to Quirinal and Vatican left
                            Italy last night. Understanding exists between Italy and Germany that
                            private property will be respected, also patent rights, sole exception
                            being necessity of state. Civilians innocent of hostile acts will not be
                            interned.</p>
                        <p>No steps yet regarding Turkey.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>